from spacy.symbols import ORTH

nlp.tokenizer.add_special_case("gimme", [
    {ORTH: "gim"},
    {ORTH: "me"},
])
doc = nlp("gimme double cheese extra large healthy pizza")
tokens = [token for token in doc]
tokens

def preprocess(text):
    doc = nlp(text)
    no_stop_words = [token.text for token in doc if not token.is_stop and not token.is_punct]
    return " ".join(no_stop_words)

import spacy

nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")

def preprocess(text):
    doc = nlp(text)
    filtered_tokens = []
    for token in doc:
        if token.is_stop or token.is_punct:
            continue
        filtered_tokens.append(token.lemma_)
    return " ".join(filtered_tokens)

def print_similarity(word_base, words_to_compare):
    token_base = nlp(word_base)
    doc = nlp(words_to_compare)
    for token in doc:
        print(f"{token.text} <-> {token_base.text}, Similarity:", token.similarity(token_base))

Using gensim's word2vec embeddings to convert text into vector¶

  1. Preprocess the text to remove stop words, punctuations and get lemma for each word
  2. Get word vectors for each of the words in a pre-processed sentece
  3. Take a mean of all word vectors to derive the numeric representation of the entire news article

In [ ]:
import spacy
nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_lg")

def preprocess_and_vectorize(text):
    doc = nlp(text)
    
    filtered_tokens = []
    
    for token in doc:
        if token.is_punct or token.is_stop:
            continue
        filtered_tokens.append(token.lemma_)
        
    return filtered_tokens

import spacy
nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_lg")

def preprocess_and_vectorize(text):
    doc = nlp(text)
    
    filtered_tokens = []
    
    for token in doc:
        if token.is_punct or token.is_stop:
            continue
        filtered_tokens.append(token.lemma_)
        
    return wv.get_mean_vector(filtered_tokens)

import re

def preprocess(text):
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub(r'[ \r\n]+', ' ', text)
    return text.strip().lower()

    matches = re.findall(pattern, text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)
    if matches:
        return matches

def get_pattern_match(pattern, text):
    matches = re.findall(pattern, text, flags=re.IGNORECASE)
    if matches:
        return matches[0]

def extract_personal_information(text):
    age = get_pattern_match('age (\d+)', text)
    full_name = get_pattern_match('Born(.*)\n', text)
    birth_date = get_pattern_match('Born.*\n(.*)\(age', text)
    birth_place = get_pattern_match('\(age.*\n(.*)', text)
    return {
        'age': int(age),
        'name': full_name.strip(),
        'birth_date': birth_date.strip(),
        'birth_place': birth_place.strip(),
    }
